Title: Relates to special supplemental nutrition program for women, infants and children
Summary: Permits WIC food vendors to submit to the department of health its current shelf price for any WIC food item that experiences low fluctuation in price and market value and a high incidence of WIC check discrepancies for approval of such price under WIC.
LawCode: Amd ยง2507, Pub Health L
ActClause: AN ACT to amend the public health law, in relation to a special supplemental nutrition program for women, infants and children
